{\b0 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
If trial court erred by inserting phrase \u8220\'3for another\u8221\'3f in first special issue to jury in capital murder prosecution, in which jury was asked whether it found from evidence beyond a reasonable doubt that conduct of defendant that caused death of the deceased was committed deliberately and with reasonable expectation that death of the deceased or another would result, such error was harmless beyond a reasonable doubt, where undisputed evidence supported only jury\rquote s affirmative finding that defendant\rquote s conduct that caused death of the victim was committed deliberately and with reasonable expectation that the death of the victim, and no other person, would result. 
}
