Hankins v. State,
}
}
{\b0 \cf25 \f5 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 646 S.W.2d 191, 197 (Tex.Cr.App.1981)
}\b0 \cf25 \f5 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 }}
{\b0 \cf1 \f5 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (On State\rquote s Motion for Rehearing), this Court held that even when a case is dependent upon circumstantial evidence for conviction, an instruction on the law of circumstantial evidence no longer must be given by the trial court.
\par 
}
}
}
}
