{\b0 \cf1 \f5 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, delivered February 27, 1985, this Court rejected the assertion that appellant makes in this cause, that when the prosecution uses an accomplice witness to establish its case against the accused, the sufficiency of the evidence must be reviewed by examining the evidence independent of the accomplice witness\rquote  testimony in order to make the determination whether the evidence is sufficient beyond a reasonable doubt to convict the defendant of the crime which he is accused of committing.
\par 
}
}
}
}
